  • Constructor Details

    • CSVParser

      public CSVParser(Reader reader, CreatorFromRow<T> rowObjectCreator, boolean hasHeader) throws IOException
      Constructor for a CSVParser object. This is a parser read-in CSV file and parse each row into the target T object specified by the CreatorFromRow parameter. Note: headers are parsed out separately given hasHeader parameter.
      Parameters:
      reader - a general reader to satisfy different types of csv input
      rowObjectCreator - parse each row into generic object determined by parser user
      hasHeader - true if csv file has header, false otherwise
      Throws:
      IOException

  • Method Details

    • parse

      public void parse() throws FactoryFailureException, IOException
      Read-in line by line csv file to parse each row of the csv file into List where T is an object specified by parse user. If header is in csv file, header will be parsed out separately into a List of string while main body rows parsed into T. If header is not provided in csv, all row in csv will be parsed to List at end. Stores parsing result in dataNoHeaderList and headerList to be accessed through getter functions.
      Throws:
      FactoryFailureException - when row cannot be parsed into the desired object using
      IOException - when readLine() fails to read-in a row in csv

    • getParseResult

      public List<T> getParseResult()
      Getter to access the parsed list of row object excluding header. If file does not have header, dataNoHeaderList will contain the entire csv file.
      Returns:
      a list holding parsed out main body csv rows from csv file

    • getParseHeader

      public List<String> getParseHeader()
      Getter to access the list containing header of csv if any header is available
      Returns:
      a list holding header of csv file, empty if no header in provided csv
